<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> S. Morris and H. Shin (1998), 'Unique equilibrium in a model of self-fulfilling currency attacks'. <i>American Economic Review</i> 88 (3), pp. 587-97.</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> Darryl McLeod (2002), <a href="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc1/CapitalFlight.html" class="external text" title="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc1/CapitalFlight.html" rel="nofollow">'Capital flight'</a>, in the Concise Encyclopedia of Economics at the <a href="http://www.econlib.org/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.econlib.org/index.html" rel="nofollow">Library of Economics and Liberty</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> A. Banerjee (1992), 'A simple model of herd behavior'."Quarterly Journal of Economics" 107 (3), pp. 797-817.</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> S. Bikhchandani, D. Hirshleifer, and I. Welch (1992),'A theory of fads, fashions, custom, and cultural change as informational cascades'."Journal of Political Economy" 100 (5), pp. 992-1026.</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> V. Chari and P. Kehoe (2004), 'Financial crises as herds: overturning the critiques'. "Journal of Economic Theory" 119, pp. 128-150.</li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> C. Avery and P. Zemsky (1998), ' Multidimensional Uncertainty and Herd Behavior in Financial Markets'. "American Economic Review" 88, pp. 724-748.</li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> M. Cipriani and A. Guarino (2008) 'Herd Behavior and Contagion in Financial Markets'. "The B.E. Journal of Theoretical Economics" 8(1) (Contributions), Article 24, pp. 1-54.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Financial_crisis&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~sternfin/crisis/" class="external text" title="http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~sternfin/crisis/" rel="nofollow">NYU Stern on Finance</a> - Blog explaining the Financial Crisis (follow link to research blog run by Stern faculty members which deals with financial economics)</li>
<li><a href="http://crisistalk.worldbank.org/" class="external text" title="http://crisistalk.worldbank.org/" rel="nofollow">Crisis Talk</a> - <a href="/wiki/World_Bank" title="World Bank">World Bank</a> blog offering information on the unfolding crisis</li>
<li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/6958091.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/6958091.stm" rel="nofollow">Financial Crises: Lessons from History</a>. <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.voxeu.org/index.php?q=node/2327" class="external text" title="http://www.voxeu.org/index.php?q=node/2327" rel="nofollow">Rescuing our Jobs and Savings: What G7/8 Leaders Can Do</a> -- policy proposals from leading economists, sponsored by <a href="/wiki/Centre_for_Economic_Policy_Research" title="Centre for Economic Policy Research">Centre for Economic Policy Research</a> at <a href="/w/index.php?title=VOXEU.org&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="VOXEU.org (page does not exist)">VOXEU.org</a>.</li>
